  "text": "However, for a network with thousands of servers, capturing the temporal and interactive traffic features of any service is very difficult. Specifically, from the perspective of temporal analysis, a strong correlation usually exists among traffic series, where previous traffic conditions likely have a large impact on future service traffic, which is called Long Range Dependency (LRD) in traffic prediction [CITATION_1] - [CITATION_2] . Meanwhile, from the perspective of interactive analysis, some network services often communicate with each other, while others seldom send messages to peers.",
